quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,25,"Preventer of good, aggressor, and doubter,"
  50,26,"Who made [as equal] with Allāh another deity; then throw him into the severe punishment."
  50,27,"His [devil] companion will say, "
  51,19,"And from their properties was [given] the right of the [needy] petitioner and the deprived."
  51,20,"And on the earth are signs for the certain [in faith]"
  51,21,"And in yourselves. Then will you not see?"
  52,10,"And the mountains will pass on, departing{1} -",footnotes:1:Becoming dust and moving as clouds.
  52,11,"Then woe, that Day, to the deniers,"
  52,12,"Who are in [empty] discourse amusing themselves."
  53,4,"It is not but a revelation revealed,"
  53,5,"Taught to him by one intense in strength [i.e., Gabriel] -"
  53,6,"One of soundness.{1} And he rose to [his] true form{2}",footnotes:1:[i.e., strength of body and of mind.],footnotes:2:[Gabriel appeared to Muḥammad (ﷺ) at the outset of his prophethood in the angelic form in which Allāh originally created him.]
